==English==
===Etymology 1===
Abbreviation of '''M'''other '''I''''d '''L'''ike to '''F'''uck. Popularized by the film ''[[w:American Pie_(movie)|American Pie]]'' (1999).

====Pronunciation====
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /mɪɫf/
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|SAMPA]]: /<tt>mI5f</tt>/

====Noun====
{{en-noun|MILF|MILFs}}
#''(acronym)'' {{vulgar}} A (putative) [[mother]] found sexually attractive.
#*'''Quotations'''
#:Dialogue from the film ''American Pie'', 1999:
#::Male adolescent A: "Dude, that chick's a MILF!"
#::Male adolescent B: "What to hell is that?"
#::Male adolescent A: "M-I-L-F, Mom I'd Like to Fuck!"
#::Male adolescent B: "Yeah dude! Yeah!"

=====Usage note=====
''MILF'' has become a much used descriptor on the internet for pornography sites featuring women mostly between the ages of 35 and 50.

